            "id": "builder-1c67a1f3e1a347dc919e4d8c7e8a48df",
            "component": {
              "name": "Text",
              "options": {
                "text": "<p><strong>This is part 3 of the&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"https://solana.com/news/solana-scaffold-part-1-wallet-adapter?ref=solana.ghost.io\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Scaffold Series</strong></a></p><h3><strong>üçÄ What Will I Get From This?</strong></h3><ul><li>[ ] Learn where to fish for code examples.</li><li>[ ] Learn how to send some SOL.</li><li>[ ] Travel the world with Transactions.</li><li>[ ] Meet the Solana Native Programs, aka the SNP Crew.</li></ul><h3><strong>üé¨ Previously In Scaffold Starter...</strong></h3><p>Nice to see you again, friend üòÅ ! Now we are transacting!!! (ahem... I mean talking). So let's see:</p><ul><li>We connected the user wallet. ‚úÖ</li><li>We funded the user wallet. ‚úÖ</li></ul><p>Now that we have a wallet connected with funds, we can actually start putting our footprint on the blockchain. Instead of just querying data, we can start modifying the blockchain and add data to it with transactions. This is where the web3 line starts!</p><h3><strong>üöÄ What Are We Building Today?</strong></h3><p>Our goal is to send some SOL to another user:</p>"
